
[1]sackcloth

   SACK'CLOTH, n. [sack and cloth.] Cloth of which sacks are made; coarse
   cloth. This word is chiefly used in Scripture to denote a cloth or
   garment worn in mourning, distress or mortification.

   Gird you with sackcloth and mourn before Abner. 2Sam. 3.

                              Esther 4. Job 46.
